105
00:07:09,047 --> 00:07:11,147
The money it took to open this shop.

106
00:07:11,147 --> 00:07:14,147
Your father was the one who covered it, wasn't he?

107
00:07:14,147 --> 00:07:17,447
And even after that, you still received money from him.

108
00:07:17,447 --> 00:07:21,247
Until he recently refused to give you any more, isn't that right?

109
00:07:21,247 --> 00:07:22,847
Who told you that?

110
00:07:22,847 --> 00:07:25,647
Your elder brother, Rokurou.

111
00:07:25,647 --> 00:07:28,427
That jerk, Rokurou.

112
00:07:28,427 --> 00:07:32,431
My brother's the one who relied on dad to fund his movies!

113
00:07:32,431 --> 00:07:33,747
But since he didn't give him much,

114
00:07:33,747 --> 00:07:36,147
he still had to take out loans!

115
00:07:38,437 --> 00:07:43,047
Actually, the company I ran went bankrupt recently.

116
00:07:43,047 --> 00:07:45,547
And my father, who had always supported me financially,

117
00:07:45,547 --> 00:07:48,447
refused to bail me out just like that.

118
00:07:48,647 --> 00:07:52,451
And, let's talk about what you did around 6:00 this morning?

119
00:07:52,451 --> 00:07:54,047
"Kimio Taguchi (32) Third-born Son" -Of course,

120
00:07:54,047 --> 00:07:56,847
I was still as sleep around 6:00.

121
00:07:56,847 --> 00:07:58,447
Really?

122
00:07:58,447 --> 00:08:01,447
That's true.

123
00:08:01,447 --> 00:08:03,647
Actually, prior to the incident,

124
00:08:03,647 --> 00:08:07,447
there was someone who witnessed you at the scene.

125
00:08:14,847 --> 00:08:16,475
Care to explain that?

126
00:08:16,475 --> 00:08:18,477
Well... that's for... I mean...

127
00:08:18,477 --> 00:08:20,479
-Say it! -Yes.

128
00:08:20,479 --> 00:08:23,047
I went to my father's house.

129
00:08:23,047 --> 00:08:24,483
What for?

130
00:08:24,483 --> 00:08:26,047
For the money...

131
00:08:26,047 --> 00:08:29,247
With good intentions? The early in the morning?

132
00:08:29,247 --> 00:08:31,947
No. I tried to steal some...

133
00:08:31,947 --> 00:08:32,947
But...

134
00:08:34,047 --> 00:08:35,847
It isn't like I heard.

135
00:08:35,847 --> 00:08:37,947
I can't get this safe opened.

136
00:08:37,947 --> 00:08:39,447
Darn!

137
00:08:39,447 --> 00:08:41,147
Don't move!

138
00:08:41,147 --> 00:08:43,747
Who the heck are you?

139
00:08:47,347 --> 00:08:49,047
Kimio?

140
00:08:51,147 --> 00:08:52,947
What a pathetic man you are!

141
00:08:52,947 --> 00:08:55,047
To think you would act like a thief.

142
00:08:55,047 --> 00:08:57,547
I just did what Akihiko asked me.

143
00:08:57,547 --> 00:08:59,647
Akihiko, you say?

144
00:08:59,647 --> 00:09:03,547
