In order to obtain the code for the safe.

267
00:14:56,875 --> 00:14:58,138
I see.

268
00:14:58,138 --> 00:15:02,238
You saw Kimio attempt his robbery over that camera.

269
00:15:02,238 --> 00:15:04,238
And decided to kill Hisaemon

270
00:15:04,238 --> 00:15:08,638
and frame Kimio for it.

271
00:15:08,638 --> 00:15:10,889
Because even if you couldn't open the safe,

272
00:15:10,889 --> 00:15:12,891
you could inherit more this way.

273
00:15:12,891 --> 00:15:15,238
-Big bro! -I knew it.

274
00:15:15,238 --> 00:15:16,895
That's complete nonsense!

275
00:15:16,895 --> 00:15:20,238
You broke into the house this morning,

276
00:15:20,238 --> 00:15:23,238
and killed Hisaemon in this study.

277
00:15:23,238 --> 00:15:25,838
Since there aren't any neighboring houses nearby,

278
00:15:25,838 --> 00:15:29,338
there was no one around to hear the gunshot.

279
00:15:29,338 --> 00:15:32,638
Then, you ordered your double to return

280
00:15:32,638 --> 00:15:35,538
and hand over the ticket stub to you.

281
00:15:35,538 --> 00:15:38,138
That way, you could appear here as if nothing happened!

282
00:15:38,138 --> 00:15:40,038
Guess right?

283
00:15:40,038 --> 00:15:42,921
No! Absolutely wrong guess!

284
00:15:42,921 --> 00:15:44,923
Where the heck are we wrong?

285
00:15:44,923 --> 00:15:46,925
Come right out, spit it out already!

286
00:15:50,929 --> 00:15:53,238
Dad?

287
00:15:54,438 --> 00:15:58,937
Rokurou, I advise you to tell the truth for your own-sake.

288
00:15:59,138 --> 00:16:02,038
If you don't, you'll be made the culprit by mistake.

289
00:16:02,038 --> 00:16:04,638
-What did you say? -What?

290
00:16:04,638 --> 00:16:08,738
Hisaemon's death was actually an unfortunate accident.

291
00:16:08,738 --> 00:16:10,938
Right?

292
00:16:10,938 --> 00:16:12,338
What do you mean by "accident"?

293
00:16:12,338 --> 00:16:16,538
Recall the position where the body fell.

294
00:16:16,538 --> 00:16:19,338
Judging from that position,

295
00:16:19,338 --> 00:16:21,538
when Hisaemon was shot,

296
00:16:21,538 --> 00:16:24,538
he would be standing about a foot away from the shelf,

297
00:16:24,538 --> 00:16:28,038
facing the wall.

298
00:16:28,038 --> 00:16:30,438
It isn't possible to stand in front of him

299
00:16:30,438 --> 00:16:33,938
and shoot him in the chest like that.

300
00:16:33,938 --> 00:16:38,977
Also, consider the stuffed eagle that fell next to the victim's foot.

301
00:16:38,977 --> 00:16:42,981
And that branch the eagle was perched on, it was broken.

302
00:16:42,981 --> 00:16:44,983
So it was, but what does that mean?

303
00:16:45,238 --> 00:16:49,338
Rokurou, you actually witnessed the entire scene, didn't you?

304
00:16:49,338 --> 00:16:52,438
On that webcam of yours.

305
00:16:54,993 --> 00:16:56,638
Yeah, yes, it's true.

306
00:16:56,638 --> 00:16:59,338
I saw everything.

307
00:16:59,338 --> 00:17:02,238
Seeing is believing.

308
00:17:05,638 --> 00:17:09,007
Look. This is the truth.

309
00:17:12,638 --> 00:17:15,013
After Kimio fled,

310
00:17:15,013 --> 00:17:19,017
dad sat there like that for a while.

311
00:17:19,017 --> 00:17:19,838
What's...

312
00:17:19,838 --> 00:17:22,038
Does anything occur as attacks?

313
00:17:26,038 --> 00:17:29,438
So the trigger got tangled on the eagle's branch

314
00:17:29,438 --> 00:17:31,338
and caused the gun to misfire.

315
00:17:31,338 --> 00:17:33,538
That's correct.

316
00:17:33,538 --> 00:17:36,438
The way dad died wasn't by murder.

317
00:17:36,438 --> 00:17:37,938
It was an accident.

318
00:17:37,938 --> 00:17:40,138
Hey you! If you had this on video all along,

319
00:17:40,138 --> 00:17:41,738
why didn't you show us earlier?

320
00:17:41,738 --> 00:17:46,238
He tried to make Akihiko and Kimio look to be murderers

321
00:17:46,238 --> 00:17:48,438
in order to keep them from getting the inheritance.

322
00:17:48,438 --> 00:17:50,538
-What? -That was why Rokurou

323
00:17:50,538 --> 00:17:53,051
hurriedly returned from Tokushima.

324
00:17:53,238 --> 00:17:55,738
Before the body was discovered.

325
00:17:55,738 --> 00:17:57,055
He planned to recover the webcam and plant fake evidence

326
00:17:57,238 --> 00:18:02,538
that would make it seem like the crime was committed by his brothers.

327
00:18:02,538 --> 00:18:07,065
But before he could, we discovered the body.

328
00:18:07,065 --> 00:18:09,438
You jerk, how could you?

329
00:18:09,438 --> 00:18:12,538
At least I proved you two innocent,

330
00:18:12,538 --> 00:18:14,838
-you should thank me! -What?

331
00:18:14,838 --> 00:18:16,638
By the way, what becomes of our share of the inheritance?

332
00:18:16,638 --> 00:18:19,538
That's right! Anyway, just get that safe open!

333
00:18:19,538 --> 00:18:21,738
For the two that act like robbers,

334
00:18:21,738 --> 00:18:24,238
I don't think you have the right to inherit anything!

335
00:18:24,238 --> 00:18:27,085
No right to inherit anything, indeed? You "Spy Camera" brat!

336
00:18:27,085 --> 00:18:28,538
You can't just keep everything yourself!

337
00:18:28,538 --> 00:18:31,089
Knock it off already!

338
00:18:31,089 --> 00:18:35,093
Have you still not figured out Hisaemon's feelings?

339
00:18:35,093 --> 00:18:37,095
Dad's feeling?

340
00:18:37,095 --> 00:18:39,097
After Kimio fled,

341
00:18:39,338 --> 00:18:45,103
he sat in front of the safe. Hisaemon wept in sorrow!

342
00:18:45,338 --> 00:18:48,138
"Wept"? Dad did?

343
00:18:48,138 --> 00:18:50,738
How could you know such a thing?

344
00:18:50,738 --> 00:18:54,238
Hisaemon's collar and chest,

345
00:18:54,238 --> 00:18:59,117
traces of a white crystalline substance was slightly found.

346
00:18:59,117 --> 00:19:02,038
That is most likely salt.

347
00:19:02,038 --> 00:19:06,238
The tears ended up drying out on his clothes.

348
00:19:06,238 --> 00:19:09,127
And left traces of salt.

349
00:19:09,127 --> 00:19:11,738
To have left salt crystals after his tear dried,

350
00:19:11,738 --> 00:19:14,438
he must have shed a lot of them, right?

351
00:19:14,438 --> 00:19:17,538
Yes. He must have cried in deep sorrow,

352
00:19:17,538 --> 00:19:19,938
and out of great embarrassment.

353
00:19:19,938 --> 00:19:22,638
He loved and pampered you all so much.

354
00:19:22,638 --> 00:19:26,638
And yet you still cannot take care of yourselves or take responsibility.

355
00:19:26,638 --> 00:19:28,438
It was due to the pampering that

356
00:19:28,438 --> 00:19:31,938
he felt he had lead you to a life of crime.

357
00:19:31,938 --> 00:19:34,838
And finally he felt hopeless

358
00:19:34,838 --> 00:19:38,638
because he could no longer financially support you.

359
00:19:38,638 --> 00:19:40,738
No longer support, what do you mean?

360
00:19:40,738 --> 00:19:44,238
There's nothing left in this house

361
00:19:44,238 --> 00:19:46,238
that can be considered valuable.

362
00:19:46,238 --> 00:19:48,038
That can't be!

363
00:19:48,038 --> 00:19:49,638
Think about it for a moment.

364
00:19:49,638 --> 00:19:52,438
In a house as large as this one on such a steep hill,

365
00:19:52,438 --> 00:19:54,238
would a senile 70 year-old man

366
00:19:54,238 --> 00:19:57,638
live all alone and not hire any servants to help him?

367
00:19:57,638 --> 00:19:59,177
Why do you think that is?

368
00:19:59,177 --> 00:20:03,538
No longer... that means he had no money left to hire anyone?

369
00:20:03,538 --> 00:20:05,183
He likely sold all his antiques,

370
00:20:05,183 --> 00:20:10,138
and had to mortgage his house along with the land.

371
00:20:10,138 --> 00:20:13,938
No way! What the heck is the safe for, then?

372
00:20:13,938 --> 00:20:15,638
Tell me what could possibly be in there.

373
00:20:15,638 --> 00:20:18,038
Inspector.

374
00:20:18,038 --> 00:20:19,638
We have opened the safe.

375
00:20:19,638 --> 00:20:21,738
Understand.

376
00:20:21,738 --> 00:20:24,538
Why not go see for yourself?

377
00:20:27,205 --> 00:20:29,638
Oh, no. It can't be.

378
00:20:29,638 --> 00:20:33,838
Why... they're all loan contracts.

379
00:20:34,538 --> 00:20:37,215
You guys mooched him off, that's why.

380
00:20:37,438 --> 00:20:39,217
Not to mention your movie production costs,

381
00:20:39,217 --> 00:20:43,738
surf shop costs, and company operation costs.

382
00:20:45,223 --> 00:20:46,338
Gosh!

383
00:20:46,338 --> 00:20:47,538
What do we do now?

384
00:20:47,538 --> 00:20:49,227
It's all over.

385
00:20:59,238 --> 00:21:01,938
This... could this be of you three?

386
00:21:01,938 --> 00:21:03,241
Yeah.

387
00:21:03,438 --> 00:21:07,538
That's from when mom was still alive.

388
00:21:07,538 --> 00:21:10,838
That's right. It's so nostalgic.

389
00:21:29,438 --> 00:21:33,938
This photo is what Hisaemon left behind,

390
00:21:33,938 --> 00:21:37,275
his final inheritance.

391
00:21:37,275 --> 00:21:41,279
The happy memories you shared as a family.

392
00:21:41,279 --> 00:21:44,438
They're all presents in that only one photo.

393
00:21:44,438 --> 00:21:50,238
However, none of you was able to inherit that present.

394
00:21:52,338 --> 00:21:55,038
Guess not.

395
00:21:55,038 --> 00:21:57,838
Sorry, dad.

396
00:23:26,438 --> 00:23:28,238
I'm glad about our family,

397
00:23:28,238 --> 00:23:30,638
since we don't have to worry about fighting over inheritance.

398
00:23:30,638 --> 00:23:33,738
Oh, yeah, guess you're right.

399
00:23:33,738 --> 00:23:35,138
This is it.

400
00:23:35,138 --> 00:23:36,638
Dad?

401
00:23:36,638 --> 00:23:38,538
Miss.

402
00:23:38,538 --> 00:23:42,138
Please grab me all these sake bottles.

403
00:23:42,138 --> 00:23:45,138
-Yes, sir. -Hold it, dad!

404
00:23:45,138 --> 00:23:46,538
What're you doing?

405
00:23:46,538 --> 00:23:49,407
What am I doing? I'm buying sake for souvenirs.

406
00:23:49,407 --> 00:23:51,409
If it's just for a souvenir, just buy one bottle!

407
00:23:51,409 --> 00:23:54,438
-One bottle! -Don't be so stingy.

408
00:23:55,413 --> 00:23:59,038
There won't be any inheritance left at this rate.

409
00:24:01,620 --> 00:24:03,160
Next Conan's Hint:

410
00:24:03,680 --> 00:24:05,423
"Flashlight"

411
00:24:05,860 --> 00:24:08,082
Dad's probably going to give up being a detective.

412
00:24:08,082 --> 00:24:10,056
What's that you say? Mouri?

413
00:24:10,056 --> 00:24:11,040
Don't yell.

